wsdl:operation.name: Login
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation login returns new session for specified user. Valid session token which is included in the response has to be used as parameter of another operations. Specified locale is also used for assembling all text messages in the same session.

wsdl:operation.name: Logout
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Invalidates specified session. Should be called everytime the session should be closed.

wsdl:operation.name: GetSandboxes
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation getSandboxes returns list of all sandboxes. Returns list of data structure SandboxInfo which contains detail info about sandbox.

wsdl:operation.name: GetSandbox
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation getSandbox returns detail info for specified sandbox.

wsdl:operation.name: GetUser
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation getUser returns detail info about specifid user.

wsdl:operation.name: DownloadFileContent
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Returns specified file from specified sandbox. FilePath parameter is relative path to the sandbox root. It can return only sandbox files, not any file on the filesystem. Returns handler which represents data stream.

wsdl:operation.name: UploadFileContent
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation uploadFileContent writes specified data to the specified file in specified sandbox. Returns simple text code of operation result. Please don't rely on the result code. To check an error properly, you must handle the exceptions.

wsdl:operation.name: ListFiles
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Returns list of files/folders in specified folder in specified sandbox. Instance of FileInfo contains detail info about the file.

wsdl:operation.name: CopySandboxFile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation CopySandboxFile copies specified file from specified sandbox to the specified file in specified sandbox. Returns list of created files. To check an error properly, you must handle the exceptions.

wsdl:operation.name: CopyFile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: This operation is deprecated. Please, use the "CopySandboxFile" operation instead. Operation copyFile copies specified file from specified sandbox to the specified file in specified sandbox. Returns simple text code of operation result. Please don't rely on the result code. To check an error properly, you must handle the exceptions.

wsdl:operation.name: CreateSandboxFile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation createSandboxFile creates specified empty file in specified sandbox. Returns created file metadata. To check an error properly, you must handle the exceptions.

wsdl:operation.name: CreateFile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: This operation is deprecated. Use CreateSandboxFile instead. Operation createFile creates specified empty in specified sandbox. Please don't rely on the result. To check an error properly, you must handle the exceptions.

wsdl:operation.name: CreateFolder
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation createFolder creates specified new folder in specified sandbox. Please don't rely on the result. To check an error properly, you must handle the exceptions.

wsdl:operation.name: DeleteFile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation deleteFile removes specified file from specified sandbox. It can't remove folders, just files. Please don't rely on the result code. To check an error properly, you must handle the exceptions.

wsdl:operation.name: MoveSandboxFile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation moveSandboxFile moves specified file or folder from specified sandbox to the specified file/folder in specified sandbox. Returns list of created sandbox items. To check an error properly, you must handle the exceptions.

wsdl:operation.name: MoveFile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: This operation is deprecated. Please, use the "MoveSandboxFile" operation instead. Operation moveFile moves specified file from specified sandbox to the specified file in specified sandbox. Returns simple text code of operation result. Please don't rely on the result code. To check an error properly, you must handle the exceptions.

wsdl:operation.name: RenameSandboxFile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation renameSandboxFile renames specified file or folder from specified sandbox. Returns list of created (renamed) sandbox items. To check an error properly, you must handle the exceptions.

wsdl:operation.name: RenameFile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: This operation is deprecated. Please, use the "RenameSandboxFile" operation instead. Operation renameFile renames specified file from specified sandbox. Returns simple text code of operation result. Please don't rely on the result code. To check an error properly, you must handle the exceptions.

wsdl:operation.name: GetFile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation getFile returns detail info about specified file in specified sandbox. File is specified by repative path from sandbox root.

wsdl:operation.name: DeleteDirectory
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation deleteDirectory removed specified folder from specified sandbox. Folder is specified by relative path to the sandbox root. Returns simple text code of operation result. Please don't rely on the result code. To check an error properly, you must handle the exceptions.

wsdl:operation.name: ExecuteGraph
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation:
Operation executeGraph starts specified transformation graph. Graph is specified by relative path to the graph file from the root of specified sandbox. Returns runId of long type, which is ID of transformation run and you can use it as parameter for another operations. Parameter "debugEnabled" is switch, when enabled, graph edges with debug enabled create temporary files with the edge data. When "debugEnabled" is disabled, no edge data is stored nevertheless the edge has debug enabled or not. Operation is not synchronous, so the response is returned when transformation is started, it doesn't wait until it's finished.
'runtimeContext' attribute can be used to pass runtime settings (analogy for GraphRuntimeContext configuration object).
Accepted values: skipCheckConfig - enforce skipping of graph configuration check (see GraphRuntimeContext.PropertyKey)

wsdl:operation.name: GetGraphExecutionLog
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation getGraphExecutionLog returns current content of log file for specified graph run. Graph run is specified by parameter runID, which is returned by "executeGraph" operation. Since this operation may be called while the graph is still running and the log file is still growing, you can use parameter "offset" to skip some bytes which were already read. Returns handler which represents data stream

wsdl:operation.name: SetLastModified
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation setLastModified sets the modification timestamp of specified file or folder in the specified sandbox. Returns simple text code of operation result. Please don't rely on the result code. To check an error properly, you must handle the exceptions.

wsdl:operation.name: GetGraphTracking
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Operation getGraphTracking returns graph trackign info about graph run specified by runID. Graph transformation may be still running or not. Returned structure GraphTracking contains info about phases, components and their in/out ports.

wsdl:operation.name: GetGraphExecutionStatus
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Returns current status of specified graph execution. It may be either currently running graph or already finished graph. In dependence on waitForStatus parameter may return result immediately or wait for specified status, but if graph is in some of the final status (FINISHED_OK | ERROR | ABORTED), returns current status at once.

wsdl:operation.name: GetJobExecutionStatus
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Returns current status of specified graph execution. It may be either currently running graph or already finished graph. In dependence on waitForStatus parameter may return result immediately or wait for specified status, but if graph is in some of the final status (FINISHED_OK | ERROR | ABORTED), returns current status at once.

wsdl:operation.name: KillGraph
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Tries to kill currently running graph. Returns final transformation status, which should be ABORTED. If specified runID belongs to execution which is already finished, returns it's final status too. It could be FINISHED_OK or ERROR.

wsdl:operation.name: GetCheckConfigResult
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Runs checkconfig on the specified graph and returns list of problems detected in the graph.

wsdl:operation.name: GetEdgeDebugData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Returns a edge debug data for specified transformation graph and edge. It's expected, that specified graph has been executed recently and it's already finished. Returns handler which represents data stream.

wsdl:operation.name: GetViewData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Returns handler which represents data stream of "view data on component" records.

wsdl:operation.name: PrepareDataView
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Answers handle that represents data stream of "view data on component" records.

wsdl:operation.name: FetchDataView
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Answers next page from data prepared in PrepareDataView operation.

wsdl:operation.name: DisposeDataView
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Disposes all reasource created in PrepareDataView operation.

wsdl:operation.name: executeInlineGraph
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Synchronous graph execution, graph and initial engine dictionary content are input parameters for this operation.

wsdl:operation.name: executeInlineGraphAsync
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Asynchronous graph execution, graph and initial engine dictionary content are input parameters for this operation.

wsdl:operation.name: echo
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Simple method intended for testing of this WS endpoint. Accepts one String parameter which is without changes sent as response.

wsdl:operation.name: ExecuteProfilerJob
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Executes a profiler job specified by sandbox code and job file path relative to the sandbox.

wsdl:operation.name: GetProfilerJobExecutionLog
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Anwers execution log file for profiler job with given run ID, starting at given offset (if any).

wsdl:operation.name: KillJob
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Asks system to kill a job with given run ID. All child jobs (if any) are killed, too. Job result is answered as outcome of the operation: should be ABORTED if the job was running, FINISHED_OK or ERROR otherwise.

wsdl:operation.name: KillJobs
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Kills running jobs specified by filter. Returns num of successfully killed jobs.

wsdl:operation.name: GetProfilerPreviewData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Answers profiler job preview data in the form of serialized data records for given sandbox, profiler job file, initial offset and maximal record count.

wsdl:operation.name: GetProfilerReportingConsole
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Answers URL of the profiler reporting console for given sandbox code.

wsdl:operation.name: GetEdgeDebugInfoList
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Answers information about edge debug data locations corresponding to given sandbox code, job file, run ID and edge ID.

wsdl:operation.name: CreateSandbox
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Asks system to create a new sandbox with given properties and locations (if any).

wsdl:operation.name: DeleteSandbox
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Asks system to delete sandbox with given code.

wsdl:operation.name: IsCluster
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Answers whether receiving server is configured to be a cluster node. Answers 'false' for a standalone server.

wsdl:operation.name: IsPartitioning
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Answers whether receiving server is allowed to run partitioned jobs. Depends on the license.

wsdl:operation.name: GetTimeZone
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Answers default time zone of the server.

wsdl:operation.name: GetClusterNodesInfo
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Answers list of available cluster nodes known to the receiver. Answers an empty list in case of a standalone server.

wsdl:operation.name: GetChildJobs
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Returns list of children for the given runId.

wsdl:operation.name: AnalyseGraph
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: This method analyses the given graph and returns transformation plan (important specially for clustered/partitioned graphs) or null if the referenced graph is not clustered or analysis failed.

wsdl:operation.name: EncryptText
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Encrypt the given message. An algorithm and seed are set in server configuration. Encrypted messages are used to encrypt secure parameters (e.g. passwords) in transformations. Throws exception if master password has not been set.

wsdl:operation.name: IsSecureParamPasswdAvailable
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Check if the master password (a seed) for encrypting/decrypting has been set.

wsdl:operation.name: UpdateSecureParamPasswd
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Updates master password (a seed) for encrypting/decrypting.

wsdl:operation.name: ExportServerConfiguration
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Anwers server configuration (i.e. users, sandboxes, etc.) as an XML file. The content of the file depends on the operation options.

wsdl:operation.name: ImportServerConfiguration
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Performs import of given server configuration XML file. The import process is driven by operation options. An XML report is answered as operation's outcome.

wsdl:operation.name: DecryptText
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Decrypt the given message. An algorithm and seed are set in server configuration. Throws exception if master password has not been set.

wsdl:operation.name: GetCloverVersion
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Answers version string of the server.

wsdl:operation.name: GetJobExecutionHierarchy
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Returns execution info for given run ID along with all of its direct or indirect descendants.

wsdl:operation.name: SynchronizeStorageIndex
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Compares client file index to server file index. Returns List of differences.

wsdl:operation.name: FetchJndiTree
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Reads content of the JNDI tree

wsdl:operation.name: PublishRestJob
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Publishes given REST job - i.e. it is made ready for HTTP invocations.

wsdl:operation.name: UnpublishRestJob
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Unpublishes given REST job if it has bee published before.

wsdl:operation.name: GetPublishedRestJobs
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Answers list of published REST jobs.

wsdl:operation.name: IsRestJobPublishable
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Answers if given REST job can be published

wsdl:operation.name: GetServerPlatform
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Returns server platform (win/linux/mac).

wsdl:operation.name: GetRestJobUrlInfo
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Returns information about the base URL where REST jobs are published.
